# DecisionOS Distribution — domain truth (V1)

Read this before answering product, data, or onboarding questions. **If not listed here, say "not in V1" or verify in code/docs.**

## Who is who

| Term in conversation | In the system | Create how |
|---------------------|---------------|------------|
| **Distributor / client / "customer" (company)** | **`Tenant`** (`ClientId`, `Name`, `BusinessProfileId`) | **Admin → Tenants** — one per onboarded distributor |
| **Buyer / account / end customer** | **`Customer_ID` / `Customer_Name` on import rows** — not a `Tenant` | **Import only** (CSV columns or workbook `Customer_Master` + sales/AR). **No Admin "Create Customer" UI** |
| **Internal user** | **ASP.NET Identity** user + role | **Admin → Users** |

**Never** tell users to create a new Tenant for each B2B buyer. Tenants isolate dashboard, uploads, KPIs, and alerts per **distributor**.

## Weekly outcomes (what the dashboard reads)

Per **`TenantId` + `PeriodEnd` (week ending date)**:

- `KpiSnapshot` — R/Y/G from `KpiDefinition` thresholds
- `DriverValue` — ranked drivers / holdovers
- `Alert` — one top alert per week
- `WeeklyFocus` — action guidance

**KPI codes in DB (do not invent others without checking `KpiDefinitions`):**  
`GrossMargin%`, `AR_PastDue31p%`, `AP_PastDue31p%`, `DOH`, `CCC`, `NetProfit%`, `PerfectOrderRate`

## Upload modes (both exist)

| Mode | UI entry | Persistence |
|------|----------|-------------|
| **Classic** | Upload Batch → Details → per-file **Map** → Validate → Run import | `UploadedFile` + `UploadedFileColumnMap` → normalized staging → scoring |
| **Simplified** | Upload Batch → **Simplified** Detect → Verify → Import all periods | One `.xlsx`, `WorkbookAnalyzer`, `SimplifiedWorkbookImportService`, multi-`PeriodEnd` |

Services: `UploadBatchImportService` (classic), `IWeeklyScoringService` / `WeeklyScoringService` (shared scoring), `ISimplifiedWorkbookImportService`.

## What is NOT in V1 (common hallucinations)

- No **`Customer` entity / DbSet** — only fields on normalized rows
- No **live ERP/POS integration** — manual file upload only
- No **Customer CRUD** Razor pages
- **`Customer_Master` sheet** is detected in simplified import; **not** a dedicated master table yet (rows used via sales/AR linkage)
- Do not claim **all** `ReportType` values are imported in classic `RunImport` — only **Sales, Inventory, AccountsReceivable, AccountsPayable** are normalized in web batch import
- No **email** notifications for holdover assignment (in-app bell only)

## Holdover workflow (execution layer)

Imported **holdover** rows are `DriverValue` (workbook `Holdover_Actions` + scoring). **Not** the same as `ActionItem` import rows.

| Capability | Where | Notes |
|------------|-------|-------|
| **Assign follow-up** | Dashboard holdover modal → **Assigned to** | Identity user from **Admin → Users**; `WorkAssignment` + `DriverValue.Owner` |
| **Activity / comments** | Same modal → **Activity and comments** | `HoldoverComment` per driver — **not** Action Items table notes |
| **In-app notifications** | Bell → `/Notifications` | `UserNotification`; assignment + new messages |
| **Plain-language UI** | `OwnerLanguage.cs` | KPI modal, alerts, holdover copy (no jargon) |

**Flags:** `DecisionOs:Workflow:AssignmentsEnabled`, `NotificationsEnabled` (default **true** in `appsettings.json`). When off → free-text owner only.

**APIs:** `GET/POST /api/tenants/{clientId}/drivers/{id}/workflow|assign|comments`, `GET /api/users/assignable`, `GET /api/notifications/unread-count`.

## Config layers

`VerticalLibrary` → `BusinessProfile` → `Tenant` (+ `TenantKpiOverride`, `TenantDriverOverride`, `InfluencerDefinition`)

